        <Parent_String>textile weaving processes and techniques [300245451], textile construction processes and techniques [300239729], textile processes and techniques [300239669], processes and techniques by material [300053900], processes and techniques by specific type [300053003], Processes and Techniques (hierarchy name) [300053001], Activities Facet [300264090]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Non-Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Generally, the process of interlacing strands or strips of various materials, such as cane, textile, or twigs, to make materials or objects such as wicker, cloth, baskets, or wreaths. Specifically used for the process of making textile on a loom or other weaving device by interlacing warp and weft in a particular order.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese generalmente para el proceso de entrelazar hilos y bandas de variados materiales, tales como caña, textil o varillas, para fabricar materiales u objetos tales como mimbre, tela, canastos o guirnaldas. Usese especificamente para el proceso de elaboración de textiles en un telar.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wordt gewoonlijk gebruikt voor het dooreenvlechten van draden of stroken van verschillend materiaal, zoals riet, textiel of twijgen, om materialen of objecten zoals vlechtwerk, stof, manden of bloemkransen te maken. Wordt met name gebruikt voor het maken van textiel op een weefgetouw of een ander weefapparaat door middel van het ineenvlechten van schering en inslag in een bepaalde volgorde.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Geralmente, o processo de entrelaçar fios ou tiras de vários materiais, como cana, tecido ou galhos, para fazer materiais ou objetos como vime, tecido, cestos ou grinaldas. Usado especificamente para o processo de fabricação de têxteis em um tear ou outro dispositivo de tecelagem entrelaçando urdidura e trama em uma ordem particular. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一般指將各式不同材料，例如藤的莖幹、紡織原料或枝椏，以縷或條帶的形式交織，製作出編製筐籃的柳條、布、簍或花圈花環等材料或物件。特別指利用織布機或是其他織造設備，以特定順序交織經線、緯線，製作出紡織品的過程。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
